[0.000, "o", "Some remarks about the string used in the next demo:"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m- the first \"äöü\" is NFC, the second \"äöü\" is NFD\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m- \"x̂\" is two codepoints in any normalization.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m"]
[0.000, "o", "- \"ϔ\" normalization forms are all different.\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m- \"ﷺ\" is one of the worst cases regarding the expansion factor in NFKS/NFKS: 18x"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m- \"baﬄe\"~text~subchar(3)=     -- T'ﬄ'\r\n\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  \"baﬄe\"~text~upper=          -- T'BAﬄE', not BAFFLE\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[1;34m  The ligature disappears in NFK[CD] but not in NF[CD]"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[1;34m*/"]
